SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: SCHEDULE D, PAGE 2, PART V, LINE 4
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE SCHOOL'S ENDOWMENT CONSISTS OF APPROXIOMATELY 125 INDIVIDUAL FUNDS ESTABLISHED FOR A VARIETY OF PURPOSES. THE ENDOWMENT INCLUDES BOTH DONOR- RESTRICTED FUNDS AND FUNDS DESIGNATED BY THE BOARD OF TRUSTEES TO FUNCTION AS ENDOWMENT.

THE SCHOOLS HAVE EVALUATED TAX POSITIONS AND THE CERTAINTY AS TO WHETHER THOSE POSITIONS WILL BE SUSTAINED IN THE EVENT OF AN AUDIT OF TAXING AUTHORITIES AT THE FEDERAL AND STATE LEVELS. THE PRIMARY TAX POSITIONS EVALUATED ARE RELATED TO THE SCHOOLS CONTINUED QUALIFICATION AS A TAX- EXEMPT ORGANIZATION AND WHETHER THERE ARE UNRELATED BUSINESS INCOME ACTIVITIES CONDUCTED THAT WOULD BE TAXABLE. MANAGEMENT HAS DETERMINED THAT ALL INCOME TAX POSITIONS ARE MORE LIKELY THAN NOT OF BEING SUSTAINED UPON POTENTIAL AUDIT OR EXAMINATION; THEREFORE, NO DISCLOSURES OF UNCERTAIN INCOME TAX POSITIONS ARE REQUIRED.

THE WEBB SCHOOLS DISBURSED GRANTS AND OTHER ASSISTANCE TOTALING 4,490,090 BETWEEN 170 RECIPIENTS.
FORM 990 IS REVIEWED BY THE WEBB SCHOOLS CHIEF FINANCIAL OFFICER, AND IS THEN CIRCULATED TO ALL TRUSTEES BEFORE IT IS FILED.

TRUSTEES AND OFFICERS COMPLETE CONFLICT OF INTEREST STATEMENTS ON AN ANNUAL BASIS; THESE DOCUMENTS ARE REVIEWED BY THE CHIEF FINANCIAL OFFIER AND ANY EXCEPTIONS ARE REPORTED TO THE HEAD OF SCHOOLS, AUDIT COMMITTEE CHAIR AND CHAIRMAN OF THE BOARD OF TRUSTEES.

THE ADMINISTRATION AND CONSULTANTS CONDUCT MARKET RESEARCH BASED ON INDUSTRY STANDARDS IN SIMILAR ORGANIZATIONS WHEN DETERMINING COMPENSATION FOR OFFICERS AND KEY EMPLOYEES. THE BOARD OF TRUSTEES REVIEWS AND APPROVES TOTAL COMPENSATION, COMPENSATION FOR THE HEAD OF SCHOOLS, AND REVIEWS COMPENSATION PACKAGES FOR OTHER KEY EMPLOYEES. THE HEAD OF SCHOOLS APPROVES COMPENSATION FOR ALL OTHER EMPLOYEES.

GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST, WHISTLE-BLOWER AND DOCUMENT RETENTION POLICES, AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS ARE DISTRIBUTED TO THE GOVERNING BODY. THESE ITEMS ARE AVAILABLE UPON REQUEST TO OTHERS.
